docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Nov. 3 -- Evidence that a Nazi spy ring functions in Chile in close cooperation with the German Embassy, transmitting news to Berlin of the greatest importance to the Nazis and detrimental to defense of this continent, was made public today by the Inter-American Emergency Advisory Committee for Political Defense of the Continent.

docs.snippet: A firm undertone continued to mark the business in the Canadian dollar last week. While business was of fair proportions, the buying carried the dollar from 87.75 cents at the opening to 88.56 cents on Thursday. Later liquidation set the price back...
docs.lead_paragraph: A firm undertone continued to mark the business in the Canadian dollar last week. While business was of fair proportions, the buying carried the dollar from 87.75 cents at the opening to 88.56 cents on Thursday. Later liquidation set the price back at the week's close to 87.93 cents, a gain of 1/16 cent over the preceding week.
